articles.description: Grayson Allen scored 23 points and No. 9 Duke beat Georgia Tech 80-69 on Sunday night to end a two-game losing streak.
articles.headline: No. 9 Duke beats Georgia Tech to end 2-game losing streak

articles.description: Without Marvin Bagley III, Grayson Allen and a slew of freshman defeat a struggling Georgia Tech team 80-69.
articles.headline: Duke rolls to victory over Georgia Tech

images.caption: Without Marvin Bagley III, Grayson Allen and a slew of freshman defeat a struggling Georgia Tech team 80-69.

articles.description: Devin Davis scored 16 points, Armoni Brooks had a double-double and Houston throttled Tulane 73-42 on Sunday to stay in a tie for second place in the American Athletic Conference standings with Wichita State.
articles.headline: Houston dissects cold-shooting Tulane 73-42

videos.description: Shake Milton gets the ball and drains 3-pointer from deep to extend SMU's lead 16-10 in the first half against Wichita State.
videos.headline: SMU's Hilton hits big triple

videos.description: Rashard Kelly passes through SMU defenders to Shaquille Morris who slams it in.
videos.headline: Wichita State's Kelly finds Morris for jam

videos.description: Landry Shamet drains two nice 3-pointers to shrink the Shockers' deficit in the first half.
videos.headline: Shamet knocks in back-to-back triples for Wichita State

videos.description: Wichita State's Austin Reeves finds Landry Shamet and he hangs in the air for a tricky basket and gets fouled for a chance at a 3-point play.
videos.headline: Shamet finishes with tough and-1

videos.description: Shockers' Landry Shamet sends a tricky pass to Shaquille Morris who dunks it in at the beginning of the second half against SMU.
videos.headline: Shamet dishes to Morris for the flush

videos.description: Shake Milton rebounds his own miss then banks in a layup and gets fouled.
videos.headline: SMU's Milton keeps it alive for 3-point play

videos.description: Darral Willis Jr. misses a layup but Markis McDuffie rises up and throws it down for the Shockers.
videos.headline: Wichita State's McDuffie soars for putback dunk

videos.description: Shake Milton knocks in a triple from the top of the key and Wichita State defenders don't do much to stop him.
videos.headline: Milton drains easy 3 to keep SMU ahead

videos.description: Shake Milton drains his fifth basket from behind the arc for a new career-high 29 points.
videos.headline: SMU's Milton hits another triple for new career high

videos.description: Trailing by 5, Darral Willis Jr. gets the offensive board, hits the layup and draws the foul with less than 14 seconds remaining in the game.
videos.headline: Wichita State's Willis Jr. creates clutch 3-point play

videos.description: Despite Landry Shamet's 20 points and 10 assists, Shake Milton drops 33 points to lead SMU past Wichita State 83-78.
videos.headline: SMU shocks No. 7 Wichita State on the road
